content:
I will clarifily that I was not in any way aware of what I'm currently communicated when it occurred to me. It was a sudden "a-ha" moment that I didn't anticipate. Only in hindsight can I really describe it with clarity and a sense of "obviousness" that is really not obvious in the conventional sense. 

If there is anything I could suggest it is that don't expect that what I'm talking about is supposed to be right around the corner like benching 225 or a new belief like adopting xyz religion. It is plain and simple "you vs. yourself" and must be resolved through figuring out the maze you have invented for yourself in your own mind.
